def prepared_data(ticker_list,file_path):

    cols_list = []
    print('Get data for the following tickers:')
    for i in range(len(ticker_list)):
        ticker=ticker_list[i]
        print(i+1,'- ', ticker)    
        # load data
        def parse(x):
            return datetime.strptime(x, '%Y/%m/%d')

        df = read_csv(file_path,  parse_dates = ['date'], index_col=0, usecols=['date',ticker], date_parser=parse)
        df = ln_return(df)
        cols_list.append(df)

    framed_dataset = pd.concat(cols_list,axis=1)
#     print('\n',framed_dataset.head())
#     print('\n',framed_dataset.tail())
    return framed_dataset

# create a natural log return series
def ln_return(series):
    #calculate natural log return
    ln_rts = lambda y,x: (y-x)/x
    series = ln_rts(series,series.shift(1))
    return series

def backtesting(weights, retData, firstdate_index, enddate_index):
    # set-up parameters
    initial = 10000
    buy_rate = 0.001
    sell_rate = 0.002
    
    # initial lists to record the transactions
    df_balance = []
    df_date = []
    daily_weighting_list = []

    number_of_rebalance = len(weights.index)
    #-------------------------------------#
    # starts from 1st period; i=0
    # specify training and testing period
    starts_date= firstdate_index[0]
    test_starts = retData.index.get_loc(starts_date)
    ends_date= enddate_index[0]
    ends_date = retData.index.asof(ends_date)
    test_ends = retData.index.get_loc(ends_date)
    cal_set= retData.iloc[test_starts:test_ends, :]
    
    # append date
    df_date.append(weights.index[0])
    
    # deduct 1st cost and append balance
    initial = initial*(1-buy_rate)
    df_balance.append(initial)
    
    # append weightings
    db = weights.iloc[0]*initial
    daily_weighting_list.append(weights.iloc[0])
    balance = db
    
    rts = cal_set+1
    
    for j in range(1,len(cal_set.index)):
        # append date
#         df_date.append(cal_set.index[j].strftime('%Y-%m-%d'))
        df_date.append(cal_set.index[j])
        
        # calculates return changes
        daily_rts = rts.iloc[j]
        balance = daily_rts*balance
        initial = balance.sum()
        df_balance.append(initial)
        
        # append weightings
        current_weights = balance/balance.sum()
        daily_weighting_list.append(current_weights)
        
    #------------------------------------#
    # continues with 2nd period; i=1
    for i in range(1, number_of_rebalance):
        # specify training and testing period
        starts_date= firstdate_index[i]
        test_starts = retData.index.get_loc(starts_date)
        ends_date= enddate_index[i]
        ends_date = retData.index.asof(ends_date)
        test_ends = retData.index.get_loc(ends_date)
        cal_set= retData.iloc[test_starts:test_ends, :]

        # calculates the current weights and returns at rebalance date
        rts = cal_set+1
        rebalance_rts = rts.iloc[0]
        balance = balance*rebalance_rts
        initial = balance.sum()
        current_weights = balance/balance.sum()
        
        # append rebalance date
        df_date.append(weights.index[i])
        
        # append weightings
        daily_weighting_list.append(weights.iloc[i])
        diff_weights = weights.iloc[i] -current_weights
        
        # determine the trading cost rate
        cost_rates = np.zeros(diff_weights.shape[0])
        for k in range(len(diff_weights)):
            if diff_weights[k] >= 0:
                cost_rates[k] = buy_rate
            else:
                cost_rates[k] = sell_rate
                
        costs = (initial*abs(diff_weights)*cost_rates).sum()
        initial = initial - costs
        
        # weights using amount after rebalance
        db = weights.iloc[i]*initial
        
        # append balance amount
        df_balance.append(initial)
        balance = db
        
        for j in range(1,len(cal_set.index)):
#             df_date.append(cal_set.index[j].strftime('%Y-%m-%d'))
            df_date.append(cal_set.index[j])
            daily_rts = rts.iloc[j]
            balance = daily_rts*balance
            
            # append balance
            initial = balance.sum()
            df_balance.append(initial)
            
            # append weightings
            current_weights = balance/balance.sum()
            daily_weighting_list.append(current_weights)
    
    portfolio_balance = pd.DataFrame(df_balance,index = df_date, columns = ['Balance'])
    return portfolio_balance

def blacklitterman(returns, tau, P, Q, pt):
    mu = (1+returns.mean())**pt-1 # monthly
    sigma = returns.cov()*pt # monthly
    pi1 = mu
    ts = tau * sigma
    Omega = np.dot(np.dot(P,ts),P.T) * np.eye(Q.shape[0])
    middle = linalg.inv(np.dot(np.dot(P,ts),P.T) + Omega)
    er = np.expand_dims(pi1,axis=0).T + np.dot(np.dot(np.dot(ts,P.T),middle),(Q - np.expand_dims(np.dot(P,pi1.T),axis=1)))
    posteriorSigma = sigma + ts -np.dot(ts.dot(P.T).dot(middle).dot(P),ts)
    return [er, posteriorSigma]

def portfolio_optimization(retData, benData, pt, period, P, Q, tau, ticker_list, firstdate_of_month, relative_views_matrix = False):
#     global weights3
    appended_data = []
    col = []
    frames = []
    w = []
    MKZ = []
    BL = []
    truncate = []
    for i in range(len(date_of_rebalance)):
        
        # specify training and testing period
    #     test_starts_date= date_of_rebalance[i]
        test_starts_date = firstdate_of_month[i]
        test_starts = retData.index.get_loc(test_starts_date)
        
        train_starts= test_starts-1-period
        train_ends= test_starts-1
        
        train_set= retData.iloc[train_starts:train_ends, :]
        bench_set= benData.iloc[train_starts:train_ends, :]
        
        # target return in specific period with equal weight
        if i == 0:
            target = (bench_set.mean() /bench_set.shape[1]).sum()
            target_ret = (1+target)**-1
            
        else:
            w = MKZ[-1].values
            targetData = (w*train_set).sum()

#         targetData = bench_set.values + 0.5*bench_set.iloc[:,1]
#         target = targetData.cumsum().iloc[-1]  
#         target_ret = (1+target)**(1/period)-1
        
        # calculate covariance matrix
        cov_mat = train_set.cov()
        cov_mat = cov_mat*pt
        
        # calculate mean returns
        avg_rets = train_set.mean()
        avg_rets = (1+avg_rets)**pt-1
        
        try:
            weights = pfopt.markowitz_portfolio(cov_mat, avg_rets, target_ret, allow_short=False)
            weights = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)
            
            if any((x < 0) or (x > 1) for x in weights):
                try:
                    s1 = MKZ[-1].values
                    s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
                except Exception:
                    s1 = np.ones(train_set.shape[1])/train_set.shape[1]
                    s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
                weights = pd.Series(s1,index= ticker_list)
                weights = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)
                
        except Exception:
            try:
                s1 = MKZ[-1].values
                s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
            except Exception:
                target = (bench_set.mean() /bench_set.shape[1]).sum()
                target_ret = (1+target)**-1
            weights = pd.Series(s1,index= ticker_list)
            
        df_weights = pd.DataFrame(weights, index = weights.index)
        df_weights.columns = [str(test_starts_date)]
        
        if relative_views_matrix == True:
            P, Q = array([P_set[i]]), Q_set[i]
        else:
            P, Q = array(P_set), Q_set[i]
            Q = Q.reshape(Q.shape[0],1)
        
        # adjusted posterior mean returns with black-litterman
        res = blacklitterman(train_set, tau, P, Q, pt)
        
        p_mean = DataFrame(res[0],index=train_set.columns,columns=[str(i+1) +' posterior_mean'])
        
        # calculate new weights
        cov_mat2 = res[1]
        cov_mat2 = cov_mat2
        avg_rets2 = pd.Series(res[0][:,0],index=retData.columns)
        
        try:
            weights2 = pfopt.markowitz_portfolio(cov_mat2, avg_rets2, target_ret, allow_short=False)
            weights3 = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights2, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)
            
            if any((x < 0) or (x > 1) for x in weights2):
                s1 = BL[-1].values
                s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
                weights2 = pd.Series(s1,index= ticker_list)
                weights3 = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights2, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)
                
        except Exception:
            try:
                weights2 = pfopt.markowitz_portfolio(cov_mat, avg_rets, target_ret, allow_short=False)
                
                if any((x < 0) or (x > 1) for x in weights2):
                    try:
                        s1 = BL[-1].values
                        s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
                    except Exception:
                        s1 = np.ones(train_set.shape[1])/train_set.shape[1]
                        weights2 = pd.Series(s1,index= ticker_list)
                        weights3 = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights2, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)   
                    
            except Exception:
                s1 = BL[-1].values
                s1 =s1.reshape((s1.shape[1], s1.shape[0]))[0]
                weights2 = pd.Series(s1,index= ticker_list)
                weights3 = pfopt.truncate_weights(weights2, min_weight=0.01, rescale=True)
                
        # Save Table
        df_weights2 = pd.DataFrame(weights2, index = weights2.index)
        df_weights2.columns = [str(test_starts_date)]
        
        df_weights3 = pd.DataFrame(weights3, index = weights3.index)
        df_weights3.columns = [str(test_starts_date)]
        
        MKZ.append(df_weights)
        BL.append(df_weights2)
        truncate.append(df_weights3)
        
    # concate weights
    BL_weights = pd.concat(BL,axis=1)
    BL_weights = BL_weights.T
    
    truncate_weights = pd.concat(truncate,axis=1)
    truncate_weights = truncate_weights.T
    
    MKZ_weights = pd.concat(MKZ,axis=1)
    MKZ_weights = MKZ_weights.T
    
    return BL_weights, truncate_weights, MKZ_weights

def weight_scaler(lower,upper, weights, columns_name):
    scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(lower, upper))
    data = weights.iloc[:,1].values.reshape(weights.shape[0],1)
    scaled_weight = scaler.fit_transform(data).reshape(1,weights.shape[0])

    df_test1 = DataFrame(1-scaled_weight[0],index = weights.index, columns = [columns_name[0]])
    df_test2 = DataFrame(scaled_weight[0],index = weights.index, columns = [columns_name[1]])
    scaled_weight = pd.concat([df_test1,df_test2],axis=1)
    return scaled_weight

# create absolute views
def create_absolute_views_and_link_matrix(names,views):
    c = len(names)
    P = zeros([c, c])
#     print('P shape: ',P.shape)
    for i in range(c):
        P[i][i] = 1
#     P_duplicate = P.copy()
#     P = P.reshape(1,P.shape[0],P.shape[1])
#     for i in range(1,len(date_of_rebalance)):
#         P = np.insert(P,-1,P_duplicate, axis=0)
#     P = array([P])
    
    Q_list =[]
    for i in range(len(date_of_rebalance)):
        lmd = firstdate_of_month[i]
        df= views.loc[str(lmd)]
        Q_list.append(df)

    Q = pd.concat(Q_list,axis=1).values
    Q = Q.T
#     print('Q shape: ',Q.shape)
    return P, Q


# create relative views
def create_relative_views_and_link_matrix(names, views):   
    views = views.iloc[:,0] - views.iloc[:,1]
    Q = abs(views).values
    Q = Q.reshape(Q.shape[0],1)
    views = views.values
    P = zeros([len(views),len(names)])
    for i in range(len(views)):
        if views[i]>0:
            P[i][0],P[i][1] = 1, -1
            
        else:
            P[i][0],P[i][1] = -1, 1
    
    P = array(P)
    return P, Q
